60|$|<b>Hare-Lip,</b> {{crushed by}} this metaphysical defeat, {{remained}} silent, {{and the old}} man went on. Often and often, though this narrative must not be clogged by the details, was Granser's tale interrupted while the boys squabbled among themselves. Also, among themselves they kept up a constant, low-voiced exchange of explanation and conjecture, as they strove to follow the old man into his unknown and vanished world.|$|E
